<p>
  Dhruv Patel is a familiar face that many around the Triangle area recognize for his involvement in the startup ecosystem. He currently serves as Director of Investor Relations for the CED located in downtown Durham.
</p>

<p>
  I had the pleasure of sitting down with Dhruv to discuss how the CED has evolved over the 32 years of involvement in the startup ecosystem.
</p>

<h4>
  Tell us about the history of the CED
</h4>

<p>
  “The CED is a 32 year old entrepreneur support organization created when there was just IBM and Glaxo in the RTP. There was not a lot in the startup ecosystem. CED was founded by a VC, an attorney, and a banker who worked with startups. The idea was to give entrepreneurs a place to go, as chambers of commerce did not seem the best place to grow and create.”
</p>

